-- Dijsselbloem Says No Models Used in Restructuring Programs
-- B y   M a u d   v a n   G a a l
-- 2013-03-25T18:27:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-25/dijsselbloem-says-no-models-used-in-restructuring-programs.html
Cyprus is “specific case with
exceptional challenges which required the bail-in measures we
have agreed upon yesterday,” Eurogroup chairman Jeroen
Dijsselbloem says in statement.
* “Macro-economic adjustment programs are tailor-made to the
situation of the country concerned and no models or templates
are used”
* Note: Saving Cyprus Means Nobody Safe as Europe Breaks More
